"What I was doing at work wasn't working." If you have ever felt like that, then this book is worth a look.

Sprints offer a path to solve big problems, test new ideas, get more done, and do it faster. A sprint in this case refers to Google Venture's unique five-day process for answering critical questions through prototyping and testing ideas with customers. This book is a DYI guide for conducting a sprint to help you answer pressing business questions about which products and services your organization should produce.

